# Dairo + FastAPI

This starter was scaffolded by `dairo init fastapi`. It is a FastAPI app with an
outbound send route and an inbound webhook handler that verifies delivery
signatures.

## Files

- `main.py` — `app = FastAPI()`: `POST /api/dairo/send` and the inbound webhook
  handler at `POST {{inbox_route}}`.

## 1. Set your API key

```sh
cp .env.example .env
```

```text
DAIRO_API_KEY=dairo_...
DAIRO_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
```

`Dairo()` reads `DAIRO_API_KEY` from the environment. Load `.env` with your
preferred tool (e.g. `python-dotenv`) or export the vars in your shell.

## 2. Install and run

```sh
{{install_cmd}}
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

## 3. Register the webhook

```sh
dairo webhook create --url https://<your-tunnel>{{inbox_route}} --event {{webhook_event}}
```

Local development:

```sh
dairo listen --forward-to http://localhost:8000{{inbox_route}}
```

## Raw body gotcha

`await request.body()` returns the **raw bytes**. Dairo signs over those bytes,
so verify before `json.loads`. `verify_webhook` raises `WebhookVerificationError`
on any failure (bad signature or stale timestamp).
